      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of \"meritocracy\" is a convenient myth used to mask inherited advantage and systemic barriers. It falsely presumes a level playing field that simply does not exist due to centuries of discriminatory practices. When wealth accumulation is predicated on historical advantage—such as access to quality education or housing in redlined neighborhoods—then the resulting wealth is not purely \"earned.\" Therefore, challenging the myth of meritocracy is essential to revealing how current economic disparities are rooted in structural injustice, not individual failing.",
